ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I can always get good feedback from professors.

Research in Progress is a seminar course in which PhD students of the department report their results and prospects of their thesis research. I would recommend this course to other students especially first year students because in this course they will learn many skills useful for their thesis researches.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: By taking this course, I got to know the research interests of many labs in our department. I also learnt some skills such as how to introduce a research project, how to present figures and how to express ideas logically and clearly. So this course definitely contributed much to my research and future study.
